    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Broad, shallow, airtight wooden cases within pipe organs that receive wind from the bellows and distribute it by means of channels or grooves to the pipes of a division.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken voor brede, ondiepe en luchtdichte houten omhulsels in een pijporgel, die wind opvangen uit de blaasbalgen en deze door middel van kanalen of goten verdelen over de pijpen van een afdeling.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052403/Van Dale Groot Woordenboek (1998)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>位於管風琴內淺而寬的密閉木箱，將由風箱所送入的風，藉由排管或溝槽引導至某一音型的音管。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Breiter, flacher, luftdichter Holzkasten in Pfeifenorgeln, der Wind aus einem Balg aufnimmt und durch Kanäle oder Kerben zu den Pfeifen eines Orgelwerkes weiterleitet.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
